02,281,000\nlast week and $391,875,000 in this\nweek last year.\nWashington cleared $22,667,000\nthis week against $23,905,000 last\nweek. This is a decrease of 11 per\ncent from the same week last year.\nBusiness failures for the week\nending May 1, as reported by Brad\nstreet\u2019s Journal, New York, number\n444. which compare with 420 last\nweek, 349 in the like week of 1929,\n425 in 1928, 384 in 1927 and 405\nin 1928.\nMarket Gossip\nA violent speculative storm shook the market from stem to\nstem on Friday, and. in the heaviest volume of trading since\nlast November 13. stock prices plunged downward with little or\nno evidence of support. The handiwork of the \"Big Bears\" wa*\nseen in a good deal of the last-minute selling, which delayed the\nticker 45 minutes and made the best of the blue chip stocks look\nunusually weak. The utilities as a group lost 13 points; the\nrails only one-tenth of a point; the industrials 414 points, and\nthe composite average of 99 stocks nearly six points.\nExperts have been pointing out in these articles the imminence\nof the reaction, which in some sections of the market has been\nmore severe than expected. The market as a whole has lost 48\nper cent of the ground covered in the January-to-April 15 ad\nvance, while about half of the distance covered by United States\nSteel, Westinghouse, General Electric, and other favorites has\nbeen surrendered.\nWith the rediscount rate at 3 per eent, a world-wide easy\nmoney situation, an improving prospect in important industries,\nbetter co-operation between the Government and industrial\nheads in working for the business revival, and, from the stock\nmarket stand oint. the shake-out in fast-travelling stocks well\non the way to completion, the market should not give a better\naccount of itself. It is time to look for a rally in the better\ngrade of industrial stocks, a list of which is given in the next\nparagraph.\nPivotal Stock Leader*\nOne of the leading wire houses\nin the Street which turned from\nits temporarily bearish stand on\nthe market just a few days ago\nto a definitely bullish attitude,\nregards the market as being dis\ntinctly in a buying range. It\nlists the following issues as the\nstocks which will lead the up\nturn, namely. United/ States Steel,\nGeneral Motors, American Can,\nGeneral Electric, Standard Oil of\nNew Jersey, Radio, and Consoli\ndated Gas of New York.\nTobacco Stock*\nThis group of stocks has shown\nconsistent growth in recent years,\nwith the total consumption of\ncigarettes representing a gain of\n12.3 per cent over the total in\nthe, previous year. Reflecting the\nsubstantial sales expansion, earn\nings of the principal producers\nincreased markedly despite large\nadvertising expenditures.\nAggregate Income surpassed by\noWsiis\nARE SOARING\nNEW YORK, May 3. \u2014Stdck\nexchange members\u2019 borrowings at\nthe end of April amounted to\n$5,063,131,359, an increase of\n$406,829,020 over the March 31\ntotal.\nThe present aggregate of ex\nchange loans compares with the\npeak of $8,549,383,797 established\non September 30 last year, and\nwith the low of $2,767,400, re\nported for May 31, 1926.\nA year ago, on April 30, 1929,\nloans to members totalled $6,-\n774,930,395.\nLoans advanced by New York\nbanks and trust companies to\nstock exchange brokers repre\nsented $3,819,476,750 of the de\nmand loans and $589,587,018 of\nthe time loans in the aggregate,\nagainst $3,519,382,700 demand and\n$506,204,000 time loans at the\nend of March.\nPrivate bankers and foreign\nagencies advanced $543,442,591 in\ndemand loans and $110,625,000\nin time funds, compared with\n5532.778.P39 and $97,937,000, re\nspectively, on March 31.\nCotton Marts\nNEW YORK\nNEW YORK, May 2 (I.N.B.)Cotton\nfuture* were ateady at the cloae today\nwith price* off 6 te 1* point*. May\ncloaed at *16.3*, July at *1( 60, Octo\nber (old) at *l4.(t, October (new) at\n*14.*7. December (eld) at *14.*6,\nDecember (new) at *14.(7, January\n(old) at *l*.*(, January