e financial district pro\u00ab~\nfesses to see a definite forward\ntrend. The first quarterly results\nfor this year show that the in\ndustry as a whole is making a\nprogress in the face of subnormal\ngeneral business conditions.\nStocks in this group which should\nwarrant attention include Air\nReduction, Allied Chemical and\nDye, Mathieson Alkali, Union\nCarbide and Carbon, and Colum-A\nbian Carbon.\n1 11\nINCREASESTEEt\nOPERATIONS\nSteel operations, barometer of\nAmerican prosperity, showed an\nappreciable gain during the week\nended April 19, according to the\nweekly review of the Commerce\nDepartment yesterday.\nThe steel plants were operat\ning at a greater rate during that\ntime than for the three-year\naverage of 1923-25, but were con\nsiderably below the high 192 J\nlevel.\nThe volume of business, as\nmeasured by check payments,\nfell off somewhat from the pre\nceding week, and was substan\ntially below that of the corre\nsponding week last year.\nProduction of bituminous coal\nwas about 2 per cent below the\npreceding week and 6 per cent\nbelow 1929. Petroleum produc\ntion, unchanged from the preced-\nI ing week, was 4 per cent below\nthe 1929 figure.\nBusiness failures were far less\nnumerous than during the same\nWestvaco Chlorine\nNet Off in Quarter\nWestvaco Chlorine Products\nCorporation shows net profits of\n$239,762, after depreciation, Fed\neral taxes and other charges,\nequivalent after dividend require\nments on preferred to 89*/a cents\nper share on 225,155 no par\nshares of common stock.\nThis compares with earnings\nof $1.16 per share for the first\nquarter of 1929 based on the\npresent number of shares out\nstanding.\nPRODUCE SHIPMENTS\nCar-lot ahlpmenta raportad for th*\nentire United State* for Thursday,\nMay 1:\nApple*\u2014New York. 25; Oregon, I;\nVirginia. 9; Waahinfton. 101; W**t\nVirginia. 4. Other* 3. Total 14T.\nCabbace \u2014Alabama. 23; Florida, S;\nMi**ia*ippi, 14; South Carolina. 143;\nTexas, 22. Other* 17. Total 223.\nOnion*\u2